{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17621160","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17621160"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T15:50:05+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T15:50:05+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16674"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"16674","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/16674"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.05,0.75,0,0.15,0.05]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9365"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"75913"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"9365","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/9365"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16674"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61420"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"5326"},{"type":"tags","id":"5417"},{"type":"tags","id":"5528"},{"type":"tags","id":"11204"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"22162"},{"type":"contributions","id":"22164"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"75913","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/75913"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EPublic health researchers are studying the relationship between food environments and population health outcomes in urban areas.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes a food swamp?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["An area where cultural food preferences are not catered for","A region with an abundance of unhealthy food outlets relative to healthy options","A neighbourhood where fresh food is prohibitively expensive","A location where food safety standards are poorly enforced","An area with no food retailers within walking distance"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EA \u003Cstrong\u003Eregion with an abundance of unhealthy food outlets relative to healthy options\u003C/strong\u003E accurately describes a food swamp. These areas are characterised by a high density of fast food restaurants, convenience stores, and retailers selling predominantly processed foods, with limited access to fresh, nutritious food options.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EA neighbourhood where fresh food is prohibitively expensive\u003C/strong\u003E: A region with poor access to fresh, affordable food is called a food desert, not a food swamp. \u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAn area with no food retailers within walking distance\u003C/strong\u003E. This is a factor that can contribute to an area being a food desert.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EA location where food safety standards are poorly enforced\u003C/strong\u003E: this relates to food regulation rather than the relative availability of healthy versus unhealthy food options.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAn area where cultural food preferences are not catered for\u003C/strong\u003E: this describes a problem with cultural food access, rather than a the balance between healthy and unhealthy food options.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EFood swamps are associated with poor dietary choices and increased rates of obesity and diet-related chronic diseases in affected communities. The overwhelming presence of unhealthy food options makes it more difficult for residents to maintain healthy eating habits.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["A food swamp is an area where unhealthy food options greatly outnumber healthy food options.","Food swamps are characterized by a high density of fast food outlets, convenience stores, and processed food retailers.","Food swamps contribute to poor dietary choices and increased risk of obesity in affected communities."],"references":["Needham C, Strugnell C, Allender S, Orellana L. Beyond food swamps and food deserts: exploring urban Australian food retail environment typologies. Public Health Nutr. Published online January 13, 2022. doi:10.1017/S136898002200009X","Cooksey-Stowers K, Schwartz MB, Brownell KD. Food Swamps Predict Obesity Rates Better Than Food Deserts in the United States. Int J Environ Res Public Health. 2017;14(11):1366. Published 2017 Nov 14. doi:10.3390/ijerph14111366"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61420"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16674"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61420","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/61420"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-01T13:45:38+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-01T13:46:06+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9365"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"75913"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta"